relation: References the subject areas that belong to the project. Each subject area is contained in a sub-element called RefPresentationCatalog.
References the logical fact tables that belong to the project. Each fact table is contained in a sub-element called RefLogicalTable.
References the application roles that belong to the project. Each application role is contained in a sub-element called RefGroup.
References the users that belong to the project. Each user is contained in a sub-element called RefUser.
References the variables that belong to the project. Each variable is contained in a sub-element called RefVariable.
References the initialization blocks that belong to the project. Each initialization block is contained in a sub-element called RefInitBlock.
References the list catalogs that belong to the project. Each list catalog is contained in a sub-element called RefListCatalog.
References the presentation tables that belong to the project. Each presentation table is contained in a sub-element called RefPresentationTable.
References the presentation columns that belong to the project. Each presentation column is contained in a sub-element called RefPresentationColumn.
References the presentation hierarchies that belong to the project. Each presentation hierarchy is contained in a sub-element called RefPresentationHierarchy.
References the presentation levels that belong to the project. Each presentation level is contained in a sub-element called RefPresentationLevel.

References any subject areas that do not belong to the project, but that are mapped to logical objects that do belong to the project. Each subject area is contained in a sub-element called RefPresentationCatalog.

References any presentation tables that do not belong to the project, but that are mapped to logical objects that do belong to the project. Each presentation table is contained in a sub-element called RefPresentationTable.

References any presentation columns that do not belong to the project, but that are mapped to logical objects that do belong to the project. Each presentation column is contained in a sub-element called RefPresentationColumn.

References any presentation hierarchies that do not belong to the project, but that are mapped to logical objects that do belong to the project. Each presentation hierarchy is contained in a sub-element called RefPresentationHierarchy.

References any presentation levels that do not belong to the project, but that are mapped to logical objects that do belong to the project. Each subject area is contained in a sub-element called RefPresentationLevel.
